							li.fragment Pano and video pano
							li.fragment Model
							li.fragment Video and video controls
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 A-Frame!
				section.slide-block
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 A-Frame facts
						p Framework on top of Three.JS
						p Open-source, version 0.7.0 as of Sept. 27th, 2017.
						p.fragment Focus on virtual reality experiences.
						p.fragment Still good for AR, general 3D interactives
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 How A-Frame works
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 HTML5 Custom elements
						p.fragment Allow you to write HTML-like syntax for 3D objects on the web.
						p.fragment Can use stadard DOM selection APIs like #[code document.querySelector] (or jQuery!) to manipulate 3D objects
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 Example (360 video):
						pre
							code
								|&lt;a-scene&gt;
								|
								|  &lt;a-assets&gt;
								|
								|    &lt;video id="video-texture" src="assets/test-video.mp4" autoplay muted crossorigin="anonymous" playsinline -webkit-playsinline&gt;&lt;/video&gt;
								|
								|  &lt;/a-assets&gt;
								|
								|  &lt;a-videosphere src="#video-texture" rotation="0 255 0"&gt;&lt;/a-videosphere&gt;
								|
								|&lt;/a-scene&gt;
					section(class="vertical-slide credited-section" data-background-iframe="https://aframe.io/aframe/examples/boilerplate/360-video/")
						.credit
							h6 A-Frame #[a(href="https://aframe.io/examples/showcase/videosphere/") example 360 videosphere]
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 Abstracts three.js
						p.fragment A-Frame's HTML-like syntax makes it a breeze to build
						p.fragment Set attributes to manipulate values like rotation, position and scale easily
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 Everything in memory
						p A-Frame keeps its changes in memory to avoid the performance hit of writing to the DOM.
						p.fragment But that means you won't see any changes in the DOM inspector üò¨
						p.fragment Luckily it comes with...
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 Visual inspector
						p.fragment Placing objects in 3D space is a challenge!
						p.fragment Visual inspector the perfect way get in and messy - just hit #[code ctrl/cmd-alt-a]!
					section.vertical-slide
